-08-17 17:17:03','<h2>Generally...</h2>\r\nAll current Napier University students are welcome to join NUAC. Most of ourÂ new members are complete beginners and we provide equipment and also tuition.\r\n\r\nArchers with previous experience are also very welcome. You can join the ClubÂ at any time of the year and you don\'t need to attend every session. HoweverÂ for best results, we recommend that you start early on in the academic yearÂ and attend as many practice sessions as you can.\r\n<h2>Mailing list</h2>\r\nIf you haven\'t done so yet, please subscribe to our mailing list by entering your email address in the \"Mailing list\" field at the right of this page.\r\n\r\nYou don\'t need to do this if you signedÂ up at the Freshers Fair in September 2011.\r\n<h2>Where and When?</h2>\r\nOur outdoor home venue is the Graduation Field round the side of CraiglockhartÂ Campus, between the building and Colinton Road - NOT the sports centre. <a href=\"http://www.lothianbuses.com\" target=\"_new\">LRT</a>Â buses 4, 10, 27 and 45.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?q=55.918231,-3.240913&amp;num=1&amp;t=h&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;sll=53.800651,-4.064941&amp;sspn=6.881357,14.941406&amp;hl=en&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;ll=55.923143,-3.239422&amp;spn=0.016832,0.036478&amp;z=14&amp;iwloc=near&amp;output=embed\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" width=\"425\" height=\"350\"></iframe>\r\n<small><a style=\"color: #0000ff; text-align: left;\" href=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?q=55.918231,-3.240913&amp;num=1&amp;t=h&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;sll=53.800651,-4.064941&amp;sspn=6.881357,14.941406&amp;hl=en&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;ll=55.923143,-3.239422&amp;spn=0.016832,0.036478&amp;z=14&amp;iwloc=near&amp;source=embed\">View Larger Map</a></small>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold;\">How much?</span>\r\n\r\nTo be confirmed soon.\r\n\r\n<!--Session Membership. Attending your first three practice sessions of the academic\r\nyear costs Â£1 a time. From the fourth session onwards it costs Â£2 a time. If\r\nyou pay annual membership then these fees no longer apply.\r\n\r\nAnnual Membership. Joining the club costs Â£10 for the year, but you must also\r\njoin Napier Students Association. This costs an additional Â£15(?), which you\r\ncan pay either through the club or at NSA HQ directly. Annual membership for\r\nthe year covers the use of club\'s equipment and affiliation to the national\r\ngoverning bodies, which helps with the insurance. Cash is acceptable, naturally,\r\nor cheques made payable to \"NSA Club Accounts - Archery\".\r\n->','Join us','','inherit','closed','open','','34-revision-8','','','2011-08-17 17:17:03','2011-08-17 17:17:03','',34,'http://webhost2.burstfire.net/~napierar/?p=77',0,'revision','',0),(39,1,'2011-08-17 15:22:05','2011-08-17 15:22:05','<h2>Generally...</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>All current Napier University students are welcome to join NUAC. Most of our \r\nnew members are complete beginners and we provide equipment and also tuition. \r\nArchers with previous experience are also very welcome. You can join the Club \r\nat any time of the year and you don\'t need to attend every session. However \r\nfor best results, we recommend that you start early on in the academic year \r\nand attend as many practice sessions as you can.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Mailing list</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you haven\'t done so yet, please subscribe to our mailing list by sending \r\n  an email to napierarchery@googlemail.com. You don\'t need to do this if you signed \r\n  up at the Freshers Fair.</p>\r\n  \r\n<h2>Where and When?</h2>\r\n<p><img src =\"/images/globe.jpg\" alt =\"a globe\">\r\n  <img src =\"/images/clock.jpg\" alt =\"a clock\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our outdoor home venue is the Graduation Field round the side of Craiglockhart \r\n  Campus, between the building and Colinton Road - NOT the sports centre. <a href=\"http://www.lothianbuses.com\" target=\"_new\">LRT</a> \r\n  buses 4, 10, 27 and 45.</p>\r\n<p>We also go to Heriot-Watt University to shoot longer distances. <a href=\"http://www.lothianbuses.com\" target=\"_new\">LRT</a> \r\n  buses 25, 34 and 45.</p>\r\n<p>We train a couple of days in a week, depending on the weather. All welcome at any stage of the year - just drop us an email to arrange a meeting! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our venue for the indoor season (well from now until Christmas anyway) is at \r\n  Meadowbank Stadium, located on London Road. See <a href=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?hl=en&ie=UTF8&q=Meadowbank%2BStadium&fb=1&gl=uk&hq=Meadowbank%2BStadium&view=map&cid=5528823726134404296&ved=0CH0QpQY&ei=RBCzTNyXOp3PjAeCuNmqDg&hnear=&z=15&iwloc=A\" target=\"_blank\">Google \r\n  Maps</a>, LRT buses 4, 5, 15/15A, 26, 44/44A.</p>\r\n<p>Indoor practice times are as follows:</p>\r\n<UL>\r\n  <li>Mondays 20:30-22:00</li>\r\n  <li>Fridays 18:00-22:00</li>\r\n  </UL>\r\n<p>During the outdoor season (March/April to September) we shoot at Craiglockhart \r\n  Campus, on the field between the campus building and Colinton Road. Practice \r\n  times as advertised. </p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How much?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Session Membership. Attending your first three practice sessions of the academic \r\n  year costs Â£1 a time. From the fourth session onwards it costs Â£2 a time. If \r\n  you pay annual membership then these fees no longer apply.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Annual Membership. Joining the club costs Â£10 for the year, but you must also \r\n  join Napier Students Association. This costs an additional Â£15(?), which you \r\n  can pay either through the club or at NSA HQ directly. Annual membership for \r\n  the year covers the use of club\'s equipment and affiliation to the national \r\n  governing bodies, which helps with the insurance. Cash is acceptable, naturally, \r\n  or cheques made payable to \"NSA Club Accounts - Archery\".</p>','Join us','','inherit','closed','open','','34-revision-5','','','2011-08-17 15:22:05','2011-08-17 15:22:05','',34,'http://webhost2.burstfire.net/~napi