ithin short walking distance that go to most part of Edinburgh. Indoor training will start by the end of September, likely Week 3 of Semester 1.\r\nIndoor Training Times:\r\n- Friday 8 - 10 pm\r\n- Sunday 4 - 7 pm\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?q=55.918231,-3.240913&num=1&t=h&vpsrc=6&sll=53.800651,-4.064941&sspn=6.881357,14.941406&hl=en&ie=UTF8&ll=55.923143,-3.239422&spn=0.016832,0.036478&z=14&iwloc=near&output=embed\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" width=\"650\" height=\"350\"></iframe>\r\n<small><a style=\"color: #0000ff; text-align: left;\" href=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?q=55.918231,-3.240913&num=1&t=h&vpsrc=6&sll=53.800651,-4.064941&sspn=6.881357,14.941406&hl=en&ie=UTF8&ll=55.923143,-3.239422&spn=0.016832,0.036478&z=14&iwloc=near&source=embed\">View Larger Map</a></small>\r\n\r\n<h2>How much?</h2>\r\nMembership fees for the whole year starting from September are as follows\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Napier Student: Â£30</li>\r\n	<li>Napier Alumni: Â£35</li>\r\n	<li>Other: Â£40</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>We will be offering Â£5 discount off the student membership price at the Freshers\' Fayre!</strong> (new members only).\r\n\r\nTo become a member with us, you also need to be a member of the Sports Union. That provides all members with insurance, discounts at certain pubs and clubs and allows you to represent the University. We can take care of your affiliation to the Sports Union or you can join through other club or directly at the NSA.','Join Us','','inherit','closed','open','','34-revision-21','','','2011-09-04 20:25:53','2011-09-04 19:25:53','',34,'http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/183/34-revision-21',0,'revision','',0),(102,1,'2011-08-17 18:03:39','2011-08-17 18:03:39','<h3>Novice Guides and Reference Material</h3>\r\nBelow you will find links to useful reference materials, as well as some guides about going to competitions etc.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/documents/novice_com