04-19.pdf\">Current Club Consititution</a>Â (April 2011)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Score Sheets</h2>\r\nLinks for blank score sheets used in competition or within the club for scored shoots.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/documents/Napier%20Scoresheet.xls\" target=\"_2\">Napier Scoresheet</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Documents','','inherit','closed','open','','94-revision-19','','','2011-09-07 21:34:51','2011-09-07 20:34:51','',94,'http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/198/94-revision-19',0,'revision','',0),(200,1,'2011-09-09 17:53:26','2011-09-09 16:53:26','All current Napier University students are welcome to join NUAC. Most of our new members are complete beginners and we provide equipment and also tuition.\r\n\r\nArchers with previous experience are also very welcome. You can join the Club at any time of the year and you don\'t need to attend every session. However for best results, we recommend that you start early on in the academic year and attend as many practice sessions as you can.\r\n\r\n<h2>Mailing list</h2>\r\nIf you haven\'t done so yet, please subscribe to our mailing list by entering your email address in the \"Mailing list\" field at the right of this page.\r\n\r\nYou don\'t need to do this if you signed up at the Freshers Fair in September 2011.\r\n<h2>Where and When?</h2>\r\n<strong>The first session of the season will be held on Sunday 11th September 2011, 2:00 pm.</strong>\r\nWe will meet at Craiglockhart Campus, at the Graduation Field (all details are given below).\r\n\r\nOur outdoor home venue is the Graduation Field round the side of Craiglockhart Campus, between the building and Colinton Road - NOT the sports centre. <a href=\"http://www.lothianbuses.com\" target=\"_new\">LRT</a> buses 4, 10, 27 and 45.\r\n\r\nOur indoor home venue is the North Merchiston Club. There are plenty of bus services available within short walking distance that go to most part of Edinburgh. Indoor training will start by the end of September, likely Week 3 of Semester 1.\r\nIndoor Training Times:\r\n- Friday 8 - 10 pm\r\n- Sunday 4 - 7 pm\r\n\r\n<iframe width=\"650\" height=\"350\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" src=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps/ms?msa=0&amp;msid=214246895898223805601.0004ac84ce26c9d4f5616&amp;hl=en&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;t=m&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;ll=55.930356,-3.220024&amp;spn=0.033658,0.11158&amp;z=13&amp;output=embed\"></iframe><br /><small>View <a href=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps/ms?msa=0&amp;msid=214246895898223805601.0004ac84ce26c9d4f5616&amp;hl=en&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;t=m&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;ll=55.930356,-3.220024&amp;spn=0.033658,0.11158&amp;z=13&amp;source=embed\" style=\"color:#0000FF;text-align:left\">NUAC Map</a> in a larger map</small>\r\n\r\n<h2>How much?</h2>\r\nMembership fees for the whole year starting from September are as follows\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Napier Student: Â£30</li>\r\n	<li>Napier Alumni: Â£35</li>\r\n	<li>Other: Â£40</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>We will be offering Â£5 discount off the student membership price at the Freshers\' Fayre!</strong> (new members only).\r\n\r\nTo become a member with us, you also need to be a member of the Sports Union. That provides all members with insurance, discounts at certain pubs and clubs and allows you to represent the University. We can take care of your affiliation to the Sports Union or you can join through other club or directly at the NSA.','Join Us','','inherit','closed','open','','34-revision-23','','','2011-09-09 17:53:26','2011-09-09 16:53:26','',34,'http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/200/34-revision-23',0,'revision','',0),(201,1,'2011-09-07 21:52:55','2011-09-07 20:52:55','Check out our results below. Napier archers/teams (often) highlighted in red.\r\n<h2>2010/2011</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Scored Practice Session, Meadowbank, 29/Oct/10,Â <a href=\"http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/_results/2010_10_29_practice.html\">Results</a>, HTML</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>2009/2010</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>BUCS Outdoor Champs - DNS</li>\r\n