ort walking distance that go to most part of Edinburgh. Indoor training will start by the end of September, likely Week 3 of Semester 1.\r\nIndoor Training Times:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Friday 8 - 10 pm</li>\r\n	<li>Sunday 4 - 7 pm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<iframe width=\"650\" height=\"350\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" src=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps/ms?msa=0&amp;msid=214246895898223805601.0004ac84ce26c9d4f5616&amp;hl=en&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;t=m&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;ll=55.930356,-3.220024&amp;spn=0.033658,0.11158&amp;z=13&amp;output=embed\"></iframe><br /><small>View <a href=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps/ms?msa=0&amp;msid=214246895898223805601.0004ac84ce26c9d4f5616&amp;hl=en&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;t=m&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;ll=55.930356,-3.220024&amp;spn=0.033658,0.11158&amp;z=13&amp;source=embed\" style=\"color:#0000FF;text-align:left\">NUAC Map</a> in a larger map</small>\r\n\r\n<h2>How much?</h2>\r\nMembership fees for the whole year starting from September are as follows\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Napier Student: Â£30</li>\r\n	<li>Napier Alumni: Â£35</li>\r\n	<li>Other: Â£40</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>We will be offering Â£5 discount off the student membership price at the Freshers\' Fayre!</strong> (new members only).\r\n\r\nTo become a member with us, you also need to be a member of the Sports Union. That provides all members with insurance, discounts at certain pubs and clubs and allows you to represent the University. We can take care of your affiliation to the Sports Union or you can join through other club or directly at the NSA.','Join Us','','inherit','closed','open','','34-revision-24','','','2011-09-09 17:54:59','2011-09-09 16:54:59','',34,'http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/217/34-revision-24',0,'revision','',0),(218,1,'2011-09-03 17:55:03','2011-09-03 17:55:03','<h2>Club Email</h2>\r\nWrite to us atÂ <a href=\"mailto:napierarchery@gmail.com\">napierarchery@gmail.com</a>!\r\nWe will get back to you shortly.\r\n\r\n<h2>2011/2012 Committee and Other Office Holders</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ewan Gunn (President/Captain)</li>\r\n	<li>Jules Coynel (Vice President)</li>\r\n	<li>Piotr Wojtczuk (Vice Captain)</li>\r\n	<li>Niall Kinsella (Equipment Officer)</li>\r\n	<li>Stewart Barclay (Head Coach)</li>\r\n	<li>George Delaney (Comms)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Our Postal Address</h2>\r\nNapier University Archery Club,\r\nc/o Napier Students Association,\r\n12 Merchiston Place,\r\nEdinburgh,\r\nEH10 4NR.\r\n\r\nTel. 0131 229 8791','Contact','','inherit','closed','open','','46-revision-7','','','2011-09-03 17:55:03','2011-09-03 17:55:03','',46,'http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/218/46-revision-7',0,'revision','',0),(221,1,'2011-09-10 10:28:01','2011-09-10 09:28:01','<strong>The first session of the season will be held on Sunday 11th September 2011, 2:00 pm, at Craiglockhart Campus - Graduation Field.</strong>\r\nThat\'s where some of you had a chance to try archery at the Freshers\' Fayre on Thursday.\r\nSee <a href=\"http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/?page_id=34\" title=\"Join us\">Join Us page</a> for more information.\r\n\r\nAll experienced archers should come at 1:00 pm to prepare for the session.\r\n\r\nWe will be going to McCowans Brewhouse after the session - please come even, if you can\'t make it to the archery session.','First Session','','inherit','closed','open','','135-revision-3','','','2011-09-10 10:28:01','2011-09-10 09:28:01','',135,'http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/221/135-revision-3',0,'revision','',0),(222,1,'2011-09-10 11:34:45','2011-09-10 10:34:45','<strong>The first session of the season will be held on Sunday 11th September 2011, 2:00 pm, at Craiglockhart Campus - Graduation Field.</strong>\r\nThat\'s where some of you had a chance to try archery at the Freshers\' Fayre on Thursday.\r\nSee <a href=\"http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/join-us\" title=\"Join us\">Join Us page</a> for more information.\r\n\r\nAll experienced archers should come at 1:00 pm to prepare for the session.\r\n\r\nWe will be going to McCowans B