ease bring money to purchase Sports Union cards, if you haven\'t got one yet - see the Sports Union Cards post.</p>\n<p>See the Join us section for information on the venue.</p>','Sunday Session - INDOORS!!','','publish','closed','open','','sunday-session-indoors','','','2011-09-17 08:57:33','2011-09-17 07:57:33','',0,'http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/262/sunday-session-indoors',0,'post','',0),(263,3,'2011-09-12 17:17:28','2011-09-12 16:17:28','All current Napier University students are welcome to join NUAC. Most of our new members are complete beginners and we provide equipment and also tuition.\r\n\r\nArchers with previous experience are also very welcome. You can join the Club at any time of the year and you don\'t need to attend every session. However for best results, we recommend that you start early on in the academic year and attend as many practice sessions as you can.\r\n\r\n<h2>Mailing list</h2>\r\nIf you haven\'t done so yet, please subscribe to our mailing list by entering your email address in the \"Mailing list\" field at the right of this page.\r\n\r\nYou don\'t need to do this if you signed up at the Freshers Fair in September 2011.\r\n<h2>Where and When?</h2>\r\n<strong>The first session of the season will be held on Sunday 11th September 2011, 2:00 pm.</strong>\r\nWe will meet at Craiglockhart Campus, at the Graduation Field (all details are given below).\r\n\r\nDon\'t worry, if you can\'t make it to the first session! See the <a href=\"http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/calendars\" title=\"Calendars\">Calendar</a> and choose any other session that suits you!\r\n\r\nOur outdoor home venue is the Graduation Field round the side of Craiglockhart Campus, between the building and Colinton Road - NOT the sports centre. <a href=\"http://www.lothianbuses.com\" target=\"_new\">LRT</a> buses 4, 10, 27 and 45.\r\n\r\nOur indoor home venue is the North Merchiston Club. There are plenty of bus services available within short walking distance that go to most part of Edinburgh. Indoor training will start by the end of September, likely Week 3 of Semester 1.\r\nIndoor Training Times:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Friday 8 - 10 pm</li>\r\n	<li>Sunday 4 - 7 pm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nFor up-to-date training times and venues see the <a href=\"http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/calendars\" title=\"Calendars\">Calendars page</a>.\r\n\r\n<iframe width=\"650\" height=\"350\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" marginheight=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" src=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps/ms?msa=0&amp;msid=214246895898223805601.0004ac84ce26c9d4f5616&amp;hl=en&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;t=m&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;ll=55.930356,-3.220024&amp;spn=0.033658,0.11158&amp;z=13&amp;output=embed\"></iframe><br /><small>View <a href=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps/ms?msa=0&amp;msid=214246895898223805601.0004ac84ce26c9d4f5616&amp;hl=en&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;t=m&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;ll=55.930356,-3.220024&amp;spn=0.033658,0.11158&amp;z=13&amp;source=embed\" style=\"color:#0000FF;text-align:left\">NUAC Map</a> in a larger map</small>\r\n\r\n<h2>How much?</h2>\r\nMembership fees for the whole year starting from September are as follows\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Napier Student: Â£30</li>\r\n	<li>Napier Alumni: Â£35</li>\r\n	<li>Other: Â£40</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nTo become a member with us, you also need to be a member of the Sports Union. The cost is Â£15. That provides all members with insurance, affiliation with archery governing bodies, discounts at certain pubs and clubs and allows you to represent the University at competitions. We can take care of your affiliation to the Sports Union or you can join through other clubs or directly at the NSA.\r\nThe cards are currently being sold from 11.30am to 1.30pm and 3.00pm to 4.00pm, Monday to Friday, at the <a href=\"http://www.napierstudents.com\">NSA</a>.\r\nIf you choose to by your card directly from the NSA or through another club, please let us know your card number.','Join Us','','inherit','closed','open','','34-revision-28','','','2011-09-12 17:17:28','2011-09-12 16:17:28','',34,'http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/263/34-revision-28',0,'revision','',0),(270,1,'2011-09-26 18:16:42','2011-09-26 17:16:42','Week 4 already! How did that happen...\r\n\r\nThis is the first week of our regular 2 times per week indoor sessions at the North Merchiston Club:\r\n\r\nFridays 8 - 10 pm\r\nSundays 4 - 7 pm\r\n\r\nThese sessions will be mixed between seniors and novices for now, as seniors should still be able to stand the conditions outside during the week...\r\n\r\nWe will head to McCowans Brewhouse, our new sponsor, soon after each of these sessions. One night per week there will be free food served, provided we keep our numbers as strong as they have been! The usual 10 % discount still applies (ask Jules, if you haven\'t got a discount card yet).\r\n\r\nPlease join us at McCowans, also if you aren\'t coming to the archery session. Feel free to bring your friends! Unfortunately, at this stage, no one under 18 is allowed in the pub - but don\'t worry, we will try to organise other outings where everybody will be able to join in!\r\n\r\nSessions for seniors (at Craiglockhart): \r\n\r\nTuesday 6 pm - dark\r\nThursday 6 pm - dark\r\n\r\nWhenever possible, we will hold these sessions earlier - check the google calenar before you go!!\r\n\r\nIf any senior wants to shoot outside that time, they need to find a committee member to accompany them. Remember, at least one committee member plus ANY other person to hold a session at Craiglockhart!','Week 4 and On...','','inherit','closed','open','','268-revision-2','','','2011-09-26 18:16:42','2011-09-26 17:16:42','',268,'http://www.napierarchery.org.uk/270/268-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(272,1,'2011-09-27 21:45:53','2011-09-27 20:45:53','We will be training in Craiglockhart tomorrow from 2pm onward. This is for seniors only.\nWe should be there at least until 4pm but possibly until it gets dark. If you\'d like to come later than 4pm please let us know to make sure someone is still at Craiglockhart.'